race.comment: GEE AND TEE (5) is going okay and looks well placed up in trip now. She battled home over a mile at Moe last time and is bred to run the distance. Suspect she is the clear main beneficiary of LUFITAAH being scratched. RHINESTONE RORY (2) is a 29 start maiden but going okay of late and will be rock hard fit. Holds each way appeal. WET 'N' DRY (4) is another long term maiden. The run two back at Warrnambool was solid and he'll have no issue running the trip. BAGPIPES (9) is lightly raced and could be an improver at career start three and out to this distance. Liked the improvement STREAMALOT (8) showed up in trip at Gunbower last start. Keep safe.
